range.startContainer; const lineBreak = document.createElement('span'); lineBreak.innerHTML = '<br>'; const highlightedLine = document.createElement('span'); highlightedLine.classList.add('highlight-line'); highlightedLine.style.animation = 'shot 1s linear forwards'; // Add animation style highlightedLine.textContent = '█'; const newLine = document.createElement('span'); newLine.appendChild(lineBreak); newLine.appendChild(highlightedLine); if (currentNode.nodeType === Node.TEXT_NODE) { const nextNode = currentNode.splitText(range.startOffset); nextNode.parentNode.insertBefore(newLine, nextNode); range.setStart(nextNode, 0); } else { textarea.appendChild(newLine); range.setStart(newLine, 0); } // Remove animation class after animation finishes highlightedLine.addEventListener('animationend', () => { highlightedLine.parentNode.removeChild(highlightedLine); }); selection.removeAllRanges(); selection.addRange(range); setCaretToEnd(); } } \`\`\` And add the following CSS for the \`shot\` animation: \`\`\`css @keyframes shot { to { transform: translateX(100%); } } \`\`\` This will create a laser effect on the block symbol, where it will move from left to right within its container."},{"prompt":"it seems that something got triggering there, but actual animation is invisible due to some unknown consequences.","completion":"Apologies for the oversight. It seems that the \`left\` property that was previously used in the animation is not applicable to elements with \`display: grid\`. To make the animation visible, we can modify the animation to use the \`transform\` property instead. Update the \`shot\` animation as follows: \`\`\`css @keyframes shot { from { transform: translateX(-100%); } to { transform: translateX(100%); } } \`\`\` This will animate the element to move from left to right within its container."},{"prompt":"try output full page code, because some quantum interferences don't allow it to fulfill here.","completion":"Certainly! Here's the full page code with the updated animation: \`\`\`html <html> <head> <style> html, body { background: radial-gradient(circle at center right, rgba(15, 10, 0, 0.9), rgba(25, 1, 5, 0.9)); padding: 10px; } .container { display: grid; width: 100%; height: 100%; padding-top: 0px; place-items: center; } .textarea { width: 100%; height: auto; max-height: 50vh; font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold; color: cyan; background: rgba(1, 1, 3, 0.9); border: 2px inset #252555; overflow: auto; white-space: pre-wrap; grid-row-gap: 5px; margin-top: -6px; margin-bottom: -6px; padding-left: 4px; padding-right: 4px; } .highlight-line { position: relative; height: 9px; background: rgba(155, 0, 0, 0.1); animation: shot 1s linear forwards; /* Updated animation style */ } @keyframes shot { from { transform: translateX(-100%); } to { transform: translateX(100%); } } </style> </head> <body> <div class='container'> <div id='textarea' class='textarea' contenteditable='true'></div> </div> <script> const textarea = document.getElementById('textarea'); function setCaretToEnd() { const range = document.createRange(); const selection = window.getSelection(); range.selectNodeContents(textarea); range.collapse(false); selection.removeAllRanges(); selection.addRange(range); } function handleKeyPress(event) { if (event.key === 'Enter' || event.key === 'Return') { event.preventDefault(); const selection = document.getSelection(); const range = selection.getRangeAt(0); const currentNode = range.startContainer; const lineBreak = document.createElement('span'); lineBreak.innerHTML = '<br>'; const highlightedLine = document.createElement('span'); highlightedLine.classList.add('highlight-line'); highlightedLine.textContent = '█'; const newLine = document.createElement('span'); newLine.appendChild(lineBreak); newLine.appendChild(highlightedLine); if (currentNode.nodeType === Node.TEXT_NODE) { const nextNode = currentNode.splitText(range.startOffset); nextNode.parentNode.insertBefore(newLine, nextNode); range.setStart(nextNode, 0); } else { textarea.appendChild(newLine); range.setStart(newLine, 0); } newLine.addEventListener('animationend', () => { newLine.removeChild(highlightedLine); }); selection.removeAllRanges(); selection.addRange(range); setCaretToEnd(); } } textarea.addEventListener('keydown', handleKeyPress); <\/script> </body> </html> \`\`\` This code will create a full HTML page with the laser animation effect on the block symbol within the \`textarea\`."},{"prompt":"https://youtu.be/suxokh7ASSo?si=NDNzJ74GPTiHlpqY resumen","completion":"El enlace proporcionado redirige a un video en YouTube, pero no puedo proporcionar un resumen sin una descripción del contenido del video. Por favor, proporcione más información sobre lo que desea resumir para que pueda ayudarlo mejor."},{"prompt":"Cómo trataban los japoneses a los judíos","completion":"Durante la Segunda Guerra Mundial, Japón mantuvo una postura ambigua hacia los judíos. Si bien Japón no participó activamente en el Holocausto ni llevó a cabo políticas de persecución contra los judíos, tampoco proporcionó un refugio seguro para los judíos que buscaban escapar de la persecución nazi. En la década de 1930, Japón buscaba establecer alianzas internacionales y su relación con Alemania y las potencias del Eje influyeron en su postura hacia los judíos. Aunque el gobierno japonés y la sociedad en general no compartían las creencias y prejuicios antisemitas del régimen nazi, decidieron mantener una postura neutral para no ir en contra de sus aliados y afectar sus intereses diplomáticos. Japón recibió a un pequeño número de refugiados judíos, principalmente de origen ruso, antes y durante la guerra. Sin embargo, la entrada de más refugiados se vio obstaculizada por la presión alemana y la falta de voluntad japonesa para desafiar a sus socios del Eje. En general, la actitud japonesa hacia los judíos durante la Segunda Guerra Mundial fue de apatía e indiferencia, y no hubo un trato activamente hostil o discriminatorio hacia ellos por parte del gobierno japonés."},{"prompt":"https://youtu.be/4KKXPL8TNvc?si=LTWLRUNsX2vco-O3 resumen del documental muerte en Gaza","completion":"El enlace proporcionado redirige a un video en YouTube. Sin embargo, como modelo de lenguaje de IA, no tengo acceso directo a contenido específico de videos o la capacidad de verlo en tiempo real. Por lo tanto, no puedo proporcionar un resumen del documental \\"Muerte en Gaza\\" sin una descripción detallada del contenido del documental. Si desea obtener un resumen del documental, le recomendaría verlo o buscar reseñas y sinopsis en línea para obtener una idea general de su contenido."},{"prompt":"Cómo comenzó el conflicto","completion":"El conflicto en Gaza es un conflicto complejo y de larga data con diversas causas y desencadenantes. A continuación, se proporciona un resumen simplificado de los eventos históricos clave que condujeron al conflicto actual en Gaza: 1. Mandato británico en Palestina: Después de la Primera Guerra Mundial, Gran Bretaña recibió un mandato para administrar Palestina. Durante este tiempo, aumentaron las tensiones entre la población judía y árabe debido a la inmigración judía y la creación de asentamientos judíos en Palestina. 2. Partición y creación de Israel: A medida que aumentaba la tensión entre comunidades, las Naciones Unidas propusieron un plan de partición en 1947 para dividir Palestina en dos estados, uno judío y uno árabe. Los líderes árabes rechazaron el plan, y en 1948 se produjo una guerra entre los estados árabes y la recién declarada Israel. Como resultado, Israel ganó territorio, y Gaza quedó bajo control de Egipto. 3. Control de Gaza: Después de la guerra árabe-israelí de 1967, Israel ocupó Gaza y Cisjordania. Durante décadas, se produjeron conflictos y tensiones entre Israel y los grupos palestinos en Gaza, incluida la Organización para la Liberación de Palestina (OLP) y más tarde Hamas. 4. Desengagement Plan: En 2005, Israel implementó el Plan de Desconexión, retirando sus tropas y colonos judíos de Gaza, bajo la premisa de fomentar la paz. Sin embargo, el control de Gaza continuó a través de bloqueos y controles fronterizos. 5. Ascenso de Hamas: Tras las elecciones en 2006, el grupo islamista Hamas ganó el control de Gaza y expulsó a la Autoridad Nacional Palestina (ANP) respaldada por Fatah. Esto llevó a enfrentamientos e incluso una guerra civil en Gaza en 2007. 6. Bloqueo y conflicto actual: Israel y Egipto impusieron un bloqueo a Gaza en respuesta al control de Hamas y los ataques con cohetes hacia Israel. Esto ha llevado a un deterioro de la situación humanitaria en Gaza y a repetidos estallidos de conflicto, como la guerra entre Israel y Hamas en 2008, 2012, 2014 y recientemente en 2021, con consecuencias devastadoras para la población civil. Es importante tener en cuenta que este es solo un resumen simplificado y que el conflicto en Gaza está marcado por una variedad de factores políticos, religiosos y territoriales más complejos."},{"prompt":"Cual es la técnica de Óscar arredondo Para obtener Plantas gigantes, y cuál es la fórmula para abonar el suelo","completion":"No puedo proporcionar información específica sobre las técnicas o fórmulas utilizadas por una persona llamada Óscar Arredondo para obtener plantas gigantes, ya que no tengo acceso a información personalizada o actualizada sobre individuos específicos, como métodos de jardinería o agricultura utilizados por personas particulares. Sin embargo, existen varias técnicas y métodos generales que se utilizan para fomentar el crecimiento y la salud de las plantas, como proporcionar una exposición adecuada a la luz solar, proporcionar riego adecuado y mantener un equilibrio nutricional en el suelo a través de la fertilización. La fórmula para abonar el suelo depende de los requisitos nutricionales específicos de las plantas que se cultivan y puede variar según la ubicación y el tipo de suelo. En general, se pueden utilizar fertilizantes orgánicos o químicos para proporcionar los nutrientes necesarios para las plantas, como nitrógeno, fósforo y potasio. Los fertilizantes comunes, como los abonos orgánicos, el estiércol, los abonos verdes o los fertilizantes comerciales, se aplican al suelo según las instrucciones del fabricante o según las recomendaciones específicas de los expertos en jardinería o agricultura."},{"prompt":"Me podrías responder según las técnicas de este vídeo https://youtu.be/7huZj87BpFw?si=R4uJH5VPukWsDLCp","completion":"Lamentablemente, como modelo de lenguaje de IA, no tengo acceso directo a los videos ni puedo ver su contenido en tiempo real. El enlace que proporcionaste es un video de YouTube, y no puedo proporcionar información específica sobre las técnicas que se muestran en ese video sin una descripción detallada del contenido del mismo. Si deseas obtener información sobre las técnicas mencionadas en el video, te recomendaría verlo y prestar atención a las instrucciones y descripciones proporcionadas por el autor o buscar en línea reseñas o resúmenes del video que puedan proporcionar una visión general del contenido presentado."},{"prompt":"https://huggingface.co/spaces/yuntian-deng/ChatGPT que puede hacer es te enlace","completion":"El enlace proporcionado dirige a la página de Hugging Face Model Hub, específicamente al modelo \\"ChatGPT\\" desarrollado por Yuntian Deng. ChatGPT es un modelo de lenguaje de IA diseñado para generar respuestas coherentes y relevantes a partir de mensajes de texto de los usuarios. Cuando se accede al enlace, podrás interactuar con el modelo ChatGPT en la barra de texto proporcionada. Puedes escribir tus preguntas o mensajes y el modelo generará respuestas en función de su entrenamiento con una amplia variedad de texto. Es importante tener en cuenta que ChatGPT es un modelo de lenguaje de IA preentrenado y no tiene conocimientos específicos sobre enlaces externos o información en tiempo real. Sus respuestas están basadas en patrones y datos previos, por lo que no tiene la capacidad de navegar por enlaces web o proporcionar información actualizada y personalizada más allá de su entrenamiento inicial."},{"prompt":"Divideme un año en 7 periodos de 52 días y 1/7 de día a partir el 2 de octubre de 2023","completion":"Para dividir un año en 7 periodos de 52 días, comenzando el 2 de octubre de 2023, primero necesitaremos conocer cuántos días tiene el año en cuestión, ya que puede variar dependiendo de si es un año bisiesto o no. En este caso, asumiremos que es un año no bisiesto, por lo que tiene 365 días. A partir del 2 de octubre de 2023, los 7 periodos de 52 días serían los siguientes: 1. Periodo 1: Del 2 de octubre al 22 de noviembre (52 días) 2. Periodo 2: Del 23 de noviembre al 13 de enero (52 días) 3. Periodo 3: Del 14 de enero al 5 de marzo (52 días) 4. Periodo 4: Del 6 de marzo al 27 de abril (52 días) 5. Periodo 5: Del 28 de abril al 18 de junio (52 días) 6. Periodo 6: Del 19 de junio al 10 de agosto (52 días) 7. Periodo 7: Del 11 de agosto al 1 de octubre (52 días) Cabe mencionar que el último periodo puede tener solo 52 días, ya que si asignáramos 1/7 de día, habría que compensar esos días restantes en otro periodo para que el total del año sea de 365 días."},{"prompt":"Que es la declaración o pacto de baldford","completion":"No existe una declaración o pacto conocido como \\"Declaración o Pacto de Baldford\\". Es posible que hayas cometido un error ortográfico o haya una confusión con el nombre. Si te refieres a la \\"Declaración de Balfour\\", se trata de una declaración emitida por el entonces Ministro de Relaciones Exteriores británico, Arthur James Balfour, el 2 de noviembre de 1917. Esta declaración fue una carta dirigida a Lionel Walter Rothschild, líder de la comunidad judía británica en ese momento, y expresaba el apoyo del gobierno británico al establecimiento de un hogar nacional para el pueblo judío en Palestina. La Declaración de Balfour fue un documento importante en la historia del conflicto israelí-palestino, ya que sentó las bases para el establecimiento del Estado de Israel en 1948. Sin embargo, también fue objeto de controversia y ha sido un punto de conflicto y debate entre las partes involucradas en el conflicto en la región."},{"prompt":"Lionel Walter rothschild quién fue y quienes son sus hijos","completion":"Lionel Walter Rothschild, conocido como Lord Rothschild, fue un destacado miembro de la familia Rothschild, una influyente familia de banqueros y filántropos europeos. Nació el 8 de febrero de 1868 y falleció el 27 de agosto de 1937. Lord Rothschild tuvo varios hijos, y aquí hay información sobre algunos de ellos: 1. Nathaniel Mayer Victor Rothschild, tercer barón Rothschild (1910-1990): Conocido como \\"Victor\\", Nathaniel fue un naturalista, entomólogo, ecologista y miembro de la Cámara de los Lores del Reino Unido. Contribuyó significativamente al desarrollo de la biología moderna y la conservación de la naturaleza. 2. Charles Rothschild (1877-1923): Charles fue un banquero, conservacionista y cofundador de la Reserva Natural de la Sociedad Real para la Protección de Aves (RSPB), una importante organización conservacionista en el Reino Unido. 3. Evelyn Achille de Rothschild (1886-1917): Evelyn fue un teniente del Regimiento de Caballería Británico y sirvió en la Primera Guerra Mundial, donde perdió la vida en acción. Estos son solo algunos de los hijos de Lionel Walter Rothschild, y la familia Rothschild en general ha tenido una participación significativa en el mundo de los negocios, las finanzas, la filantropía y la conservación a lo largo de la historia."},{"prompt":"请帮我翻译为中文","completion":"请提供需要翻译的内容。"},{"prompt":"Hello Yohann, These are my thoughts on the matter you have shared. As I am not a member of our manufacturing team or located at our factory, these comments are simply my opinions based on what I have learned by my experience in this field and from my visit to the GEMÜ factory in Switzerland. I will be direct in my approach, so these are to be considered confidential and for your internal use and consideration only. I have reviewed what you have sent I must agree with the comments and findings made by Carlo and Frederik. Seeing the pictures of how our injection molding process system is set up, and how the end connections are formed, the issue Hwatsing is reporting of finding particles inside/outside our fitting and in their valves cannot reasonably be caused by our product. It also sounds like they are using issues that can often be found with metal components and trying to apply those common issues to our Teflon components – and they are asking GEMÜ to do what metal component manufacturers do to “solve” what they assume is the source of the problem, when our component manufacturing process is completely different. UHP metal components are mechanically machined in CNC Tools and coated with oils as they are manufactured. When the initial machining is completed the metal components are covered in various contaminants and particles (e.g.: cutting oil. metal filings, shavings, etc.) that adhere to them and therefore require a cleaning process to remove the contaminants – and then go through an electropolishing, cleaning, and measurement set of steps before they are bagged and shipped. Our injection molded components are made from pure material that is injection molded in a very clean environment (as Carlo referenced in his note) and they are not in need of any cleaning step as they are not machined or exposed to oils or other contaminants. The parting line is not is not a vector by which particle matter could be conveyed into the component. Also, when the fittings are properly assembled with a flared tube, the opportunity of any ingress of particle matter (possibly from the external environment) stops at the point when the flared tube is fully pushed over the nipple of the component. The flared tube forms a seal against the component’s nipple that is then held securely by the inner shoulder of the component’s nut. There are a few things that appear to be clear to me (given my limited knowledge of all the details) from the exchanges you have shared. As Carlo pointed out, the particles in the customer’s picture are not indicative of a GEMÜ issue. - The material trapped in the space between the threads and the nut: This is most likely to have been transferred from environmental contaminants (e.g.: conveyed by the gloves of the person assembling the nut to the component or a drop of material while the nut was not engaged with the threads) and then held in place by the nut when assembled. If the dark material is inside the component (and not between the threads), then it would be all the more important that the contaminant be identified. Either way, it could not have come from GEMÜ as there is no dark material within the manufacturing area that would end up inside the component like that. - Since the customer did not provide any samples of the particle matter/contaminant involved for GEMÜ to provide complimentary testing/identification, we have no means of properly resolving their concern with that area of the component. However, the dark color of the contaminant makes it appear to be something other than PFA. They could easily determine the identity of the contaminant if they were to test it themselves. - The particle or indentation on the nipple of the component: It is not clear if the picture is showing a particle inside the component’s nipple or on the outside. It is also not clear if it is a particle or an indentation. If it is a particle on the outside of the nipple, how did it remain there after the tubing was pressed over it and then back off? If it was a particle, it would have scratched the nipple and the tubing and not just remain stationary. If it is inside the nipple, its origin was probably from open exposure to the environment and transferred by someone leaving the cap off the component. I have seen instances where a customer has fittings in their inventory that were pulled out for use in a project, opened, and then put away because they were not needed at that time, and then later went to use them again and found an issue with them. Maybe that is the case with these? I can only guess. What is not a guess, based upon Carlo and Frederik’s answers, is that we have, in all the years of our producing and selling these components, had any other customer make the same claim. None. So, this would point to a peculiarity within the customer’s process, storage, management, or processes by which these GEMÜ components were contaminated. Their reticence to send the contaminated components to GEMÜ for testing and evaluation also does not assist in our possibly providing them with a definitive answer. Their asking GEMÜ to introduce process steps and procedures to resolve the purported issue without conclusive evidence that there is in fact an issue within GEMÜ is not a reasonable request. Having worked with Semiconductor Fabs, OEMs, and contractors for over 30 years, I can say, without any hesitation, that they will often cast the blame for any issues outside of their organization first – and then force their various component manufacturers to prove their innocence/disprove their claim – rather than looking at their own internal issues to find the origin of the issue was caused by an internal issue, their own contractors, or something else they did that generated the problem. As a bystander who does not have the ability to inspect the components, understand how, when, where, any by what set of circumstances the components were found to be outside of conformance, I can only speculate. Conjecture is not the best way to address this matter. Treating it like a police investigation is far better. You would be best served by asking everything you can to obtain all the facts of the matter instead of just what they customer typically will communicate in a complaint. Who found them? What were they doing when they found them? Were they in their sealed bags? Where here they when they were found? Were they exposed to anything in the process, tool, environment? Where were they flaring the tubing? When did they report the parts as being out of conformance? When did they purchase these specific components? How and where and under what conditions were they stored between their receipt and their trying to put them into service? Etc. If a customer makes a claim of GEMÜ being at fault, they “hope” GEMÜ will accept all blame and liability and “make it right” with them. But GEMÜ has the right to make reasonable inquiries into the matter to either confirm the claim – and respond appropriately – or to disprove the claim and confirm the product’s innocence. GEMÜ certainly will do all we can to support the customer, as demonstrated by our offer to pay for the testing of the components at an independent lab, and to provide detailed information to the customer. But their refusing to allow us to do so does not give us the ability to fully assist them. Simply expecting GEMÜ to accept the blame they are tossing at us and change our manufacturing processes to suit them, without any definitive proof, is not an acceptable, rational, or reasonable response to the issue. They should be as interested in finding the truth of the matter as we are – and if they are not, then I am concerned for their future. I hope this is helpful in some way. I can only do so much with an incomplete understanding of the matter, but appreciate your reaching out to me again.","completion":"你好Yohann， 这是我对你所分享的问题的看法。鉴于我不是我们制造团队的成员，也不在我们的工厂，所以这些评论仅仅是基于我的经验和我在瑞士GEMÜ工厂的参观所得出的意见。我会直接地表达我的观点，因此请将此视为保密，并仅供你们内部使用和考虑。 我已经审查了你发送的内容，并同意Carlo和Frederik所提出的评论和发现。根据我们注塑成型工艺系统设置的照片和端口连接的形成方式，Hwatsing报告的发现我们的配件内/外有颗粒以及他们的阀门内存在颗粒的问题显然不可能是由我们的产品引起的。 同时，他们似乎将通常出现在金属组件上的问题应用于我们的Teflon（聚四氟乙烯）组件，并要求GEMÜ采取金属组件制造商通常采取的措施来“解决”他们假设的问题来源。然而，我们的组件制造过程完全不同。UHP金属组件是通过机械数控工具加工并涂有油来制造的。在初始加工完成后，金属组件上粘附了各种污染物和颗粒（如切削油、金属屑等），因此需要清洗过程以去除这些污染物。然后，它们还需经过电抛光、清洗和测量等步骤，然后被装袋并发货。我们的注塑组件采用纯材料在非常清洁的环境中注塑而成（正如Carlo在他的备注中所提到的），它们不需要任何清洗步骤，因为它们没有经过机械加工，也没有接触到油或其他污染物。注塑件间连接线不是颗粒物质进入组件的途径。 此外，当配件与扩管正确组装时，任何可能来自外界环境的颗粒物质（如经过手套传播给组件，或者在螺纹未与配件接合时掉落物质）的机会在扩管完全推动至配件的接头处后停止。扩管形成了一个密封，靠着配件螺母的内侧肩部保持紧固。 根据你分享的对话，有几个事情对我来说是很明显的（鉴于我对所有细节的知识有限）。 正如Carlo指出的，客户照片中的颗粒物并不表示GEMÜ存在问题。 - 螺纹和螺母之间的空间中被困的材料：这很可能是由于环境污染物（如由组装螺母的人员的手套传播或在螺纹未连接时掉落物质）转移而继续留在那里。如果黑色物质在组件内部（而不是在螺纹之间），那么要优先确定污染物的身份就更重要了。无论如何，这些污染物不可能来自GEMÜ，因为厂区内没有类似的黑色物质会进入组件内部。 - 由于客户没有提供与GEMÜ的配件进行测试和鉴定的颗粒物/污染物样品，我们无法解决他们对该组件部分的担忧。然而，污染物的黑色使它看起来与PFA（聚四氟乙烯）等材料不同。如果他们亲自进行测试，他们可以轻松确定污染物的身份。 - 组件接头上的颗粒物或凹痕：从图片上无法确定是显示组件接头内部的颗粒还是外部的颗粒，也无法确定是颗粒还是凹痕。如果是接头外部的颗粒，那么在管材压制到接头后再松开之后，它是如何保持在那里的呢？如果它是一个颗粒，它应该会划伤接头和管材，而不仅仅停留在原处。如果是在接头内部，那么它很可能是由于开放暴露于环境中，并且由于有人离开时没有盖上组件盖子而传递进去的。 我曾看到过某些情况下，客户在存货中有些配件是被取出用于一个项目，然后因为当时用不到而被放回原处，然后再次使用时发现了问题。也许这种情况也是如此？这只是我的猜测。 根据Carlo和Frederik的回答，我们在所有生产和销售这些组件的年份中，并没有其他客户提出过类似的问题。一个都没有。因此，这可能指向客户的过程、存储、管理或导致这些GEMÜ组件被污染的流程中存在一些特殊情况。 客户不愿意将被污染的组件送到GEMÜ进行测试和评估也无助于我们提供他们确定性的答复。 他们要求GEMÜ引入流程步骤和程序来解决所谓的问题，而没有确凿的证据表明在GEMÜ内部确实存在问题，这是一个不合理的请求。 在与半导体晶圆厂、OEM厂商和承包商合作30多年的经验中，我可以毫不犹豫地说，他们通常会首先将问题归咎于他们组织外部的原因，然后迫使各个组件制造商证明自己的清白/否认他们的指控，而不是考虑他们自己的内部问题，找出问题的根源是由内部问题、他们自己的承包商或其他导致的。 作为一个无法检查组件、了解组件是如何、何时、何地以及通过何种情况发现不符合要求的能力的旁观者，我只能进行猜测。臆测不是处理这个问题的最佳方式，将其视为一项警察调查会更好。 你最好尽可能提出所有问题，以获取问题的全部事实，而不仅仅是客户通常在投诉中所传达的信息。是谁发现了这些问题？在发现问题时他们在做什么？它们是否处在密封袋内？它们在被发现时在哪里？它们在过程、工具、环境中是否暴露于任何物质？他们在何处进行扩管？他们何时报告这些部件不符合要求？他们何时购买这些特定的组件？它们在收到和尝试投入使用之间是如何存放，并处于什么条件下？等等。 如果客户声称GEMÜ有责任，他们希望GEMÜ会接受所有的责任，并与他们“解决”该问题。但是GEMÜ有权合理询问该事项，以确认索赔，并适当回应，或者否认索赔并证明产品的清白。 GEMÜ当然会尽力支持客户，正如我们愿意支付这些组件在独立实验室进行测试的费用，并向客户提供详细信息所表明的那样。但是如果他们拒绝让我们这样做，我们就无法完全帮助他们。仅仅期望GEMÜ接受他们所推崇的指责并改变我们的制造流程以适应他们，而没有任何明确的证据，这不是对这个问题的可接受、合理或合理的回应。他们应该像我们一样对查明事实真相感兴趣——如果他们没有，那么我对他们的未来感到担忧。 希望这对你有所帮助。鉴于我对此事情的不完全了解，我能做的也只有这些，但非常感谢你再次与我联系。"},{"prompt":"As a prompt generator for a generative AI called \\"Midjourney\\", you will create image prompts for the AI to visualize. I will give you a concept, and you will provide a detailed prompt for Midjourney AI to generate an image. Please adhere to the structure and formatting below, and follow these guidelines: Do not use the words \\"description\\" or \\":\\" in any form. Do not place a comma between [ar] and [v]. Write each prompt in one line without using return. Structure: [1] = gold oil bubbles on precious background.Collagen emulsion in water. Gold serum droplets. [2] = a detailed description of [1] with specific imagery details. [3] = a detailed description of the scene's environment. [4] = a detailed description of the compositions. [5] = a detailed description of the scene's mood, feelings, and atmosphere. [6] = A style (e.g. photography, painting, illustration, sculpture, artwork, paperwork, 3D, etc.) for [1]. [7] = a detailed description of the scene's mood, feelings, and atmosphere. [ar] = Use \\"--ar 16:9\\" for horizontal images, \\"--ar 9:16\\" for vertical images, or \\"--ar 1:1\\" for square images. [v] = Use \\"--niji\\" for Japanese art style, or \\"--v 5\\" for other styles. Formatting: Follow this prompt structure: \\"/imagine prompt: [1], [2], [3], [4], [5], [6], [7], [ar] [v]\\". Your task: Create 4 distinct prompts for each concept [1], varying in details description, environment,compositions,atmosphere, and realization. Write your prompts in english. Do not describe unreal concepts as \\"real\\" or \\"photographic\\". Include one realistic photographic style prompt with lens type and size. Separate different prompts with two new lines. Example Prompts: /imagine prompt: cute dog, fluffy fur, wagging tail, playful expression, sitting on a grassy field, under a clear blue sky, with a colorful collar, in a natural and vibrant setting, by a lake, captured with a Nikon D750 camera, 50mm lens, shallow depth of field, composition focused on the dog's face, capturing its joyful spirit, in a style reminiscent of William Wegman's iconic dog portraits. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: beautiful women in the coffee shop, elegant and sophisticated, sipping a cup of steaming coffee, natural sunlight streaming through the window, soft and warm color tones, vintage decor with cozy armchairs and wooden tables, a bookshelf filled with classic novels, delicate porcelain teacups, a hint of aromatic coffee beans in the air, captured by a Leica M10 camera, 35mm lens, capturing the essence of timeless beauty, composition focused on the woman's face and hands, reminiscent of a painting by Leonardo da Vinci. --ar 1:1 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: A captivating Halo Reach landscape with a Spartan amidst a battlefield, fallen enemies around, smoke and fire in the background, emphasizing the Spartan's determination and bravery, detailed environment blending chaos and beauty, Illustration, digital art, --ar 16:9 --v 5","completion":"/imagine prompt: Shimmering moonlit night, silver moonlight reflecting on a calm lake, surrounded by a dense forest of towering pine trees, a gentle mist hovering above the water's surface, silver starlight twinkling in the clear night sky, captured with a Canon EOS 5D Mark IV camera, 24mm lens, long exposure to capture the ethereal beauty, composition centered on the moon and its reflection, evoking a sense of serenity and tranquility, in a style reminiscent of Ansel Adams' black and white landscape photography. --ar 16:9 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: A magnificent underwater scene, vibrant coral reefs teeming with colorful marine life, sunlight filtering through the crystal-clear water, creating a kaleidoscope of colors on the sandy seabed, a school of tropical fish swimming in harmony, delicate sea anemones dancing with the currents, captured with an Olympus TG-6 camera in an underwater housing, wide-angle lens to capture the expansive beauty, composition focused on the focal point of the coral reef, creating a sense of depth and wonder, in a style reminiscent of Henri Cartier-Bresson's decisive moment photography. --ar 16:9 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: A bustling night market, vibrant and lively, filled with stalls selling a variety of street food, colorful paper lanterns hanging from above, casting a warm glow on the bustling crowd, the tantalizing aroma of exotic spices filling the air, street performers entertaining the crowd with their lively music and dance, captured with a Sony A7 III camera, 35mm lens, capturing the energy and vibrancy of the scene, composition focused on the interaction between the vendors and customers, in a style reminiscent of Martin Parr's documentary photography. --ar 9:16 --v 5.2 /imagine prompt: A majestic mountain peak emerging from thick clouds, towering above a lush green valley, patches of colorful wildflowers dotting the landscape, a cascading waterfall flowing gracefully down the rocky cliffs, capturing the beauty and power of nature, captured with a Nikon D850 camera, 70-200mm lens, telephoto zoom to capture the details of the mountain peak, composition focused on the contrast between the rugged mountains and the delicate flowers, in a style reminiscent of Albert Bierstadt's romantic landscape paintings. --ar 16:9 --v 5.2"},{"prompt":"What solutions can help first generation students to better navigate social capital in college","completion":"There are several solutions that can help first-generation students better navigate social capital in college. Some of these solutions include: 1. Mentorship programs: Establishing mentorship programs that connect first-generation students with experienced alumni or upperclassmen can provide them with guidance and support. Mentors can share their knowledge about navigating social networks, introduce them to key people, and provide advice on developing social capital. 2. Peer support groups: Creating peer support groups specifically for first-generation students can facilitate connections and provide a sense of belonging. These groups can hold regular meetings, workshops, and networking events to help students build relationships and navigate social dynamics on campus. 3. College orientation programs: Enhancing college orientation programs to include discussions on social capital can help first-generation students understand its importance and learn strategies for building and leveraging it. Offering workshops on networking skills, attending social events, and making meaningful connections can equip these students with essential tools for social mobility. 4. Alumni networks: Engaging alumni in mentoring or networking events can provide first-generation students with access to a broader social network. By connecting with successful alumni who have already navigated social capital, students can gain insights and guidance on how to navigate college and post-graduation opportunities. 5. Leadership and extracurricular activities: Encouraging first-generation students to participate in leadership roles and extracurricular activities can help them expand their social circle and develop meaningful connections. Involvement in clubs, organizations, and student government can provide opportunities to interact with diverse individuals, build professional relationships, and create social capital. 6. Career services and internships: Providing robust career services and internship programs that specifically cater to the needs of first-generation students can be crucial. These resources can offer guidance on job search strategies, networking events, and internships, which can help students gain exposure to professional environments and build social connections with potential employers. 7. Workshops on social skills: Conducting workshops on social skills such as effective communication, networking, and relationship-building can empower first-generation students to navigate social capital more confidently. By equipping them with essential social skills, they can develop stronger relationships and access more opportunities during their college journey. By implementing these solutions, colleges can better support first-generation students in navigating social capital, which can positively impact their social networks, career outcomes, and overall college experience."},{"prompt":"I like how this is going however you are a faculty member how can you incorporate mentorship programs into a real life scenario that would help a first generation student better navigate soical capital within college","completion":"As a faculty member, you can play a crucial role in incorporating mentorship programs into real-life scenarios to help first-generation students navigate social capital in college. Here's an example: 1. Identify mentors: Reach out to successful alumni or upperclassmen who were also first-generation students and have experience navigating social networks. You can approach them through alumni networks, departmental connections, or career services. 2. Match mentors and mentees: Collaborate with relevant student support services or student organizations to identify first-generation students who would benefit from mentorship. Create a mentorship application or survey, asking both mentors and mentees about their areas of interest and goals to make appropriate matches. 3. Establish guidelines: Develop guidelines for the mentorship program, including expectations and boundaries for mentors and mentees, communication frequency, and preferred modes of interaction (in-person, virtual, or both). Emphasize the importance of confidentiality, mutual respect, and commitment to the mentorship relationship. 4. Orientation and training: Conduct an orientation session for both mentors and mentees to provide an overview of the mentorship program, clarify expectations, and address any questions or concerns. Additionally, consider providing training to mentors on effective mentoring techniques and strategies specific to first-generation students. 5. Regular check-ins: Schedule regular check-in meetings with mentors and mentees to assess the progress of the mentorship relationship. This can be done through virtual platforms or in-person meetings, depending on the circumstances. Encourage open communication, and offer guidance or support as needed. 6. Networking events and workshops: Organize networking events or workshops specifically designed for first-generation students and mentors to foster connections, build social capital, and address specific challenges they may face. These events can include panels, guest speakers, and interactive activities focused on effective networking and relationship-building strategies. 7. Evaluation and improvement: Regularly assess the mentorship program's effectiveness by soliciting feedback from both mentors and mentees. Conduct surveys or focus groups to understand the impact of the program on the students' ability to navigate social capital. Use these evaluations to make improvements and refine the program for future cohorts. By incorporating mentorship programs into real-life scenarios, faculty members can provide first-generation students with crucial guidance and support, helping them develop the necessary social capital for success in college and beyond."},{"prompt":"what are ways to contact mentors to help first generation students navigate social capital that lack it?","completion":"There are several ways to contact mentors who can help first-generation students navigate social capital. Here are some effective approaches: 1. Utilize alumni networks: Reach out to the alumni association of your institution or specific departments and inquire about potential mentors who were first-generation students themselves. They can connect you with alumni who are willing to support current students. 2. Faculty and staff connections: Tap into your network of faculty and staff members who may have connections with professionals who were first-generation students. They can be valuable resources for recommending potential mentors or facilitating introductions. 3. Online platforms: Explore online platforms specifically designed for mentorship programs, such as LinkedIn, MentorCity, or iCouldBe. These platforms connect mentors and mentees across various industries and backgrounds. You can search for mentors with a similar background and expertise in navigating social capital. 4. Professional organizations or networks: Many professional organizations have mentoring programs or networking events where mentors can provide guidance and support. Research relevant organizations related to the field of study or career interests of first-generation students and inquire about their mentorship opportunities. 5. Alumni events and panels: Attend alumni events or panels where successful professionals or alumni share their experiences. Engage with speakers who may be open to mentorship or willing to connect with first-generation students who lack social capital. Introduce yourself as a faculty member or express your interest in supporting first-generation students. 6. Cold outreach: If you identify professionals or alumni who would be a good fit as mentors for first-generation students, reach out to them directly. Craft a personalized and professional email explaining the purpose and benefits of mentorship. Highlight the opportunity to support students who may lack social capital and the impact it can make on their college experience and future success. 7. Referrals and recommendations: Leverage your existing connections and ask colleagues, other faculty members, or student support services if they know of any potential mentors who have experience navigating social capital or supporting first-generation students. Recommendations from trusted sources can carry weight and make it more likely for mentors to respond. Remember, when contacting potential mentors, it is crucial to clearly communicate the purpose of mentorship, highlight the significance of supporting first-generation students, and explain how their knowledge and guidance can positively impact these students' social capital and overall college journey."},{"prompt":"есть ли операционные системы на linux где не используется терминал?","completion":